                <h1>Explore the Fascinating History of Musical Theatre</h1>
                <p>Musical theatre has roots in ancient Greece, evolving through the centuries. The modern format began in the 19th century with operettas, gaining popularity with Broadway musicals in the early 20th century. Landmark shows like "Oklahoma!" and "West Side Story" defined the genre, blending storytelling and music, captivating audiences worldwide.</p>
